  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        True/False. For each of the following, write T if the statement is
        true; otherwise, write F. You do NOT need to provide explanations or show work for this problem. Throughout, let <m>G</m> and <m>G'</m> be groups.
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p>
              If there exists a homomorphism <m>\phi\,:\,G\to G'</m>, then <m>G</m> and <m>G'</m> must be isomorphic groups.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>
              There is an integer <m>n\geq 2</m> such that <m>\Z\simeq \Z_n</m>.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>
              If <m>|G|=|G'|=3</m>, then we must have <m>G\simeq G'</m>.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>
              If <m>|G|=|G'|=4</m>, then we must have <m>G\simeq G'</m>.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>
  <solution>
    <title>print=false</title>
    <ol type="a">
      <li>
        <p>
          F
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
          F
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
          T
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
